{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588363","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588363"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:06:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:06:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15132"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15132","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15132"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.7,0.22,0.04,0,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7820"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"60230"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7820","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7820"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15132"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"45650"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"619"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1201"},{"type":"tags","id":"1325"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7065"},{"type":"tags","id":"8131"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19063"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19066"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"60230","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/60230"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old man presents to the emergency department with fever, severe perineal pain, and difficulty passing urine.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements about prostatitis is correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acute prostatitis commonly causes urinary retention","Digital rectal examination is recommended to confirm diagnosis","Chronic prostatitis always has identifiable bacterial causes","Asymptomatic prostatitis requires immediate antibiotic therapy","Prostate massage helps relieve acute symptoms"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAcute bacterial prostatitis is a serious condition that can present with fever, perineal pain, and urinary symptoms. \u003Cstrong\u003EUrinary retention\u003C/strong\u003E is a common complication due to prostatic swelling and inflammation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDigital rectal examination\u003C/strong\u003E should be avoided in acute prostatitis as it is extremely painful and may lead to bacteraemia. The prostate is typically very tender and swollen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic prostatitis\u003C/strong\u003E can be either bacterial or non-bacterial, with the latter being more common. \u003Cstrong\u003EAsymptomatic inflammatory prostatitis\u003C/strong\u003E is often an incidental finding and does not require treatment. \u003Cstrong\u003EProstate massage\u003C/strong\u003E is contraindicated in acute prostatitis as it may cause bacteraemia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe most common causative organism is \u003Cem\u003EEscherichia coli\u003C/em\u003E, followed by other gram-negative bacteria.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Acute bacterial prostatitis presents with perineal pain, tender prostate, fever, and urinary symptoms including retention","Prostatitis can be classified into acute bacterial, chronic bacterial, chronic pelvic pain syndrome, and asymptomatic inflammatory prostatitis","Escherichia coli is the most common causative organism in acute bacterial prostatitis"],"references":["Khan FU, Ihsan AU, Khan HU, Jana R, Wazir J, Khongorzul P, Waqar M, Zhou X. Comprehensive overview of prostatitis. Biomed Pharmacother. 2017 Oct;94:1064-1076. doi: 10.1016/j.biopha.2017.08.016. Epub 2017 Aug 16. PMID: 28813783.","Bilsen MP, Jongeneel RMH, Schneeberger C, Platteel TN, van Nieuwkoop C, Mody L, Caterino JM, Geerlings SE, K\u00f6ves B, Wagenlehner F, Conroy SP, Visser LG, Lambregts MMC. Definitions of Urinary Tract Infection in Current Research: A Systematic Review. Open Forum Infect Dis. 2023 Jun 27;10(7):ofad332. doi: 10.1093/ofid/ofad332. PMID: 37426954; PMCID: PMC10323732","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"45650"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15132"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"45650","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/45650"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-10T11:54:24+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-10T11:54:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7820"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"60230"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"36","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/36"},"attributes